" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533601\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533601\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 05, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wzs1665702760065.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wzs1665702760065.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wzs1665702760065.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wzs1665702760065\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Generating Customized XML\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">To generate XML data, you can use the operations available from the UXMLWRITER component API.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"wzs1665702760065__context_w6568ab1b5b1_w6569ab1b5_w6570ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"wzs1665702760065__topic_d38387e1_d38388e1_d38389e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wzs1665702760065__p_d38390e1_d38391e1_d38392e1\">To generate an XML document:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"wzs1665702760065__li_d19430e1_d19431e1_d19432e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"wzs1665702760065__p_d38393e1_d38394e1_d38395e1\">For each XML document you want to generate,\n               create an instance of the UXMLWRITER component. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For example, to generate three XML documents, create three instances.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">variables\n handle uxml1\n handle uxml2\n handle uxml3\nendvariables\nnewinstance \"UXMLWRITER\", uxml1\nnewinstance \"UXMLWRITER\", uxml2\nnewinstance \"UXMLWRITER\", uxml3</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"wzs1665702760065__li_d19433e1_d19434e1_d19435e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"wzs1665702760065__p_d38396e1_d38397e1_d38398e1\">Call the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">STARTDOCUMENT</span>\n               operation for each instance. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">If you want the document to contain a header (<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;xml version=\"1.0\"\n                     encoding=\"UTF-8\"&gt;</code>), set the boolean parameter of this operation to\n                  true.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wzs1665702760065__p_d38399e1_d38400e1_d38401e1\">For example, the following will generate the\n                  header for instance uxml1 and uxml2, but not for uxml3:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">uxml1-&gt;startdocument(\"true\")\nuxml2-&gt;startdocument(1)\nuxml3-&gt;startdocument(\"false\")</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"wzs1665702760065__li_d19436e1_d19437e1_d19438e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Add XML elements, attributes and comments using the operations available on the UXMLWRITER component.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"wzs1665702760065__li_d19439e1_d19440e1_d19441e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"wzs1665702760065__p_d38402e1_d38403e1_d38404e1\">Retrieve the resulting XML documents with the\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">GETDOCUMENT</span> operation.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\"> For example, the following retrieves the resulting XML documents into a\n                  non-database field or a global variable.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">uxml1-&gt;getdocument(DUMMY, \"true\") ; document 1 &lt; 10240 bytes\nuxml2-&gt;getdocument($10, \"true\") ; document 2 &lt; 10240 bytes\n; Document 3 is more than 10240 bytes:\n$1 = uxml3-&gt;getdocument(FIELD1, \"true\")\nwhile ($1 &gt; 0)\n $1 = uxml3-&gt;getdocument($2, \"true\")\n FIELD1 = \"%%FIELD1%%%%%$1%%%\"\nendwhile</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"wzs1665702760065__note_w6571ab1b5b3b7b3b5_w6572ab1b5b3b7b3_w6573ab1b5b3b7_w6574ab1b5b3_w6575ab1b5_w6576ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">GETDOCUMENT</span> can only retrieve a maximum of 10240\n                  bytes, so you may need to issue multiple calls to this operation. This example\n                  assumes that documents 1 and 2 are known to be always smaller than 10240 bytes in\n                  size.</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"wzs1665702760065__li_d19442e1_d19443e1_d19444e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"wzs1665702760065__p_d38405e1_d38406e1_d38407e1\">Manipulate the data as required. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For example, create an XML file by using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">filedump</span>, or store the\n                  XML into the database.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"wzs1665702760065__li_d19445e1_d19446e1_d19447e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"wzs1665702760065__p_d38408e1_d38409e1_d38410e1\">Delete the instances of UXMLWRITER when they are\n               no longer required. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">The memory occupied by XML documents that are being generated is not freed until\n                  the instances are deleted. To free this memory and prevent a memory leak, it is\n                  very important to delete any unused component instances.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wzs1665702760065__p_d38411e1_d38412e1_d38413e1\">For example, the following deletes the three XML\n                  instances, and frees the memory occupied by the three XML documents.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">deleteinstance uxml1\ndeleteinstance uxml2\ndeleteinstance uxml3</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ccv1665702760000.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>UXMLWRITER</a><p>UXMLWRITER is an internal Uniface component that enables you to generate XML documents rather than having to code each character in the XML stream yourself.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533601\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533601\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Generating Customized XML Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 05, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Generating Customized XML To generate XML data, you can use the operations available from the UXMLWRITER component API. To generate an XML document: For each XML document you want to generate, create an instance of the UXMLWRITER component. For example, to generate three XML documents, create three instances. variables handle uxml1 handle uxml2 handle uxml3 endvariables newinstance \"UXMLWRITER\", uxml1 newinstance \"UXMLWRITER\", uxml2 newinstance \"UXMLWRITER\", uxml3 Copy Call the STARTDOCUMENT operation for each instance. If you want the document to contain a header ( <xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"> ), set the boolean parameter of this operation to true. For example, the following will generate the header for instance uxml1 and uxml2, but not for uxml3: uxml1->startdocument(\"true\") uxml2->startdocument(1) uxml3->startdocument(\"false\") Copy Add XML elements, attributes and comments using the operations available on the UXMLWRITER component. Retrieve the resulting XML documents with the GETDOCUMENT operation. For example, the following retrieves the resulting XML documents into a non-database field or a global variable. uxml1->getdocument(DUMMY, \"true\") ; document 1 < 10240 bytes uxml2->getdocument($10, \"true\") ; document 2 < 10240 bytes ; Document 3 is more than 10240 bytes: $1 = uxml3->getdocument(FIELD1, \"true\") while ($1 > 0) $1 = uxml3->getdocument($2, \"true\") FIELD1 = \"%%FIELD1%%%%%$1%%%\" endwhile Copy Note: GETDOCUMENT can only retrieve a maximum of 10240 bytes, so you may need to issue multiple calls to this operation. This example assumes that documents 1 and 2 are known to be always smaller than 10240 bytes in size. Manipulate the data as required. For example, create an XML file by using filedump , or store the XML into the database. Delete the instances of UXMLWRITER when they are no longer required. The memory occupied by XML documents that are being generated is not freed until the instances are deleted. To free this memory and prevent a memory leak, it is very important to delete any unused component instances. For example, the following deletes the three XML instances, and frees the memory occupied by the three XML documents. deleteinstance uxml1 deleteinstance uxml2 deleteinstance uxml3 Copy Related Links UXMLWRITER UXMLWRITER is an internal Uniface component that enables you to generate XML documents rather than having to code each character in the XML stream yourself. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}